@node "config-byte-reference" "Config Byte Reference"
@toc "saga-extended-mouse-xmouse"
@prev "command-arguments"
@next "how-it-works-simple"
@{b}Config Byte Reference@{ub}
Advanced users can customize behavior with a 2-digit hex byte:

@{code}
Bit 0 (0x01)     - Wheel enabled (sends scroll events)

Bit 1 (0x02)     - Extra buttons 4 & 5 enabled

Bits 2-3         - Reserved

Bits 4-5         - Poll speed:

00 = 5ms   (fast, may use more CPU)

01 = 10ms  (default, balanced)

10 = 20ms  (smooth, efficient)

11 = 40ms  (power saving)

Bit 6            - Reserved

Bit 7 (0x80)     - Debug mode (opens debug console)

@{plain}

@{b}Examples:@{ub}

- `0x13` = Wheel ON, Buttons ON, 10ms (default)

- `0x93` = Same but with debug console

- `0x01` = Wheel only, 5ms (no buttons)

- `0x21` = Wheel only, 20ms polling@endnode

@node "how-it-works-simple" "How It Works (Simple)"
@toc "saga-extended-mouse-xmouse"
@prev "config-byte-reference"
@next "roadmap-future-plans"
@{b}How It Works (Simple)@{ub}
@{code}
   1. XMouseD reads USB wheel counter from SAGA hardware

2. Calculates movement delta (~10ms per poll)

3. Sends standard scroll commands to Amiga

4. Apps recognize wheel and scroll normally

@{plain}

No special software in apps needed - wheel "just works" everywhere.@endnode

